{"type": "article", "id": 26475, "title": "看得到轨迹的橱柜", "description": "", "date": "2016-05-06T07:07:59Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [], "category": 25, "column": 28, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 1, "praise_count": 40, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160702115031We0cN7ZV1EMH5DRh.jpg", "contents": "\n\n<p class=\"medium-insert-active\">下面这几张图并不是什么视觉错觉，而是日本设计工作室 <a href=\"http://www.dezeen.com/tag/nendo\">Nendo</a> 制作的一个名为 Trace 的家具系列。就好像你不会在柜门前放上花瓶一样，Nendo 的设计师利用黑色金属线条将橱柜门开合的轨迹可视化，希望人们能重新审视空间、日常生活同家具间的联系。这个系列目前在纽约举办的 <a href=\"http://collectivedesignfair.com/\">Collective Design Fair</a> 上展出，展览将持续到 5 月 18 日。<br></p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-images-wide\">\n<figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702115029cRnDvYyjl6iqP1Bt.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66737288\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702115029Dhe8aS4MKbmAXRHG.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66770833\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702115030wtFMnp3dkOs8jL6V.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66737288\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160702115030v0wTANbmIR2JSlho.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.66770833\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n"}